description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a marketing and communications post with a &lt;strong&gt;difference?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our sexual health services provide an interesting subject area that will allow you to push yourself outside of your comfort zone and really feel like you make a difference!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inclusion, as part of a large and modern NHS Foundation Trust have excellent reputation for valuing and investing in our workforce with services across England including Sexual Health, Mental Health, Psychological Therapies and Addiction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a talented individual with creativity, spark and flair to work within our central team to provide support for Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland Sexual Health Service. You will be responsible for providing engaging and quality communications to share key messages and promotional resources for our service. You will need to have a good eye for story in words and pictures by producing compelling and creative content and have a passion for using social media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If this sounds like your dream job and you want to work to reduce stigma and promote positive conversations around sexual health, whilst being part of a friendly and supportive team then please apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
